WEBVTT

00:00:01.317 --> 00:00:03.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We look forward to

00:00:03.753 --> 00:00:06.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Anthony Morris’ thoughts

00:00:06.823 --> 00:00:09.859 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
presented in his talk entitled

00:00:09.859 --> 00:00:12.462 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We Have Work to Do!”

00:00:14.564 --> 00:00:18.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was a great pleasure
to hear all of the excitement

00:00:18.168 --> 00:00:22.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when the Ramapo project
was announced to all of you here,

00:00:22.972 --> 00:00:27.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I’m sure that was true
for the other thousands that are tied in.

00:00:27.977 --> 00:00:30.480 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then you saw with these videos

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:32.515 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
all the construction projects

00:00:32.515 --> 00:00:36.019 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
going on all over
—all over the earth.

00:00:36.019 --> 00:00:38.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So it’s quite interesting,

00:00:38.154 --> 00:00:42.759 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
if you think about it
from an imperfect, human perspective

00:00:42.759 --> 00:00:45.662 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(frankly, not thinking spiritually),

00:00:45.662 --> 00:00:50.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you’d say:
“Well, we just dedicated the Warwick property

00:00:50.667 --> 00:00:54.070 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“along with Wallkill recently.

00:00:54.070 --> 00:00:59.075 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now here we go down the road.”

00:01:00.810 --> 00:01:05.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the preaching work
obviously is premier.

00:01:05.815 --> 00:01:09.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that’s what this is really about
—the preaching work.

00:01:09.385 --> 00:01:11.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To support the preaching work

00:01:11.788 --> 00:01:15.058 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to continue to feed
Jehovah’s precious sheep

00:01:15.058 --> 00:01:19.963 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the way he wants them fed
involves all this construction.

00:01:19.963 --> 00:01:24.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So God wants us to have it clear.

00:01:24.467 --> 00:01:28.571 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He wants you to spread this and,
of course, it’ll come up in January.

00:01:28.571 --> 00:01:32.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Keep in mind, we have work to do.

00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:33.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Period.

00:01:33.343 --> 00:01:34.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So get over it.

00:01:39.649 --> 00:01:41.651 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t get me going on vacation.

00:01:41.651 --> 00:01:42.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ll just tell you—

00:01:42.786 --> 00:01:45.588 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I know my friends on the Governing Body,

00:01:45.588 --> 00:01:48.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I know that you need your time.

00:01:48.258 --> 00:01:52.662 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m not trying to put you on a guilt trip,
but we have a whole lot of days.

00:01:54.998 --> 00:01:57.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How do you do it
with the work that’s going on?

00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:00.737 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You try to rest up when you can;
Jehovah wants us to.

00:02:00.737 --> 00:02:03.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we have so much work to do.

00:02:03.206 --> 00:02:04.874 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we thank God for it.

00:02:04.874 --> 00:02:08.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So just to give us
a little Scriptural reminder

00:02:08.244 --> 00:02:11.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the proper attitude about work,

00:02:11.381 --> 00:02:13.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
find John chapter 5.

00:02:13.483 --> 00:02:16.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And these are
very familiar verses to all of you,

00:02:16.853 --> 00:02:19.455 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
particularly the audience here in Newburgh

00:02:19.455 --> 00:02:23.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with all these decades of faithful service.

00:02:23.059 --> 00:02:26.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We treasure your service

00:02:26.729 --> 00:02:29.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and, of course,
Jehovah certainly does.

00:02:29.499 --> 00:02:31.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you’ve worked hard for decades

00:02:31.534 --> 00:02:34.037 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—a lot of you to whom
I was talking to earlier

00:02:34.037 --> 00:02:36.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have decades in the traveling work—

00:02:36.039 --> 00:02:39.275 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so many wonderful,
hardworking brothers and sisters.

00:02:39.275 --> 00:02:42.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So here he is, Jesus, (in John chapter 5)

00:02:42.245 --> 00:02:47.050 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
facing these judgmental religious leaders

00:02:47.050 --> 00:02:50.553 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
persecuting him over curing on the Sabbath.

00:02:50.553 --> 00:02:55.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what we’re after here
is something he reveals to us in verse 17,

00:02:55.558 --> 00:02:58.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when he’s answering them:

00:02:58.761 --> 00:03:02.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“My Father has kept working until now,

00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:05.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I keep working.”

00:03:05.101 --> 00:03:07.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So the hardest worker
in the universe is Jehovah God,

00:03:07.937 --> 00:03:10.773 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Christ Jesus is right there with him.

00:03:10.773 --> 00:03:13.109 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is a worker.

00:03:13.109 --> 00:03:15.845 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His people have to be workers.

00:03:15.845 --> 00:03:19.282 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s what he expects,
and it’s such a pleasure

00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:22.719 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to serve the true God and work.

00:03:22.719 --> 00:03:26.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And another familiar verse
in 1 Corinthians chapter 15

00:03:26.890 --> 00:03:30.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
shows the proper spirit
when it comes to this matter

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:34.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of being workers,
with all the work we have to do.

00:03:34.163 --> 00:03:38.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jehovah is seeing to it
that we have all this work

00:03:38.868 --> 00:03:43.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—very familiar,
verse 58 of 1 Corinthians 15:

00:03:43.740 --> 00:03:46.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Therefore, my beloved brothers,

00:03:46.876 --> 00:03:49.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“be steadfast, immovable,

00:03:49.178 --> 00:03:52.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[notice] <i>always </i> having plenty to do

00:03:52.615 --> 00:03:55.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in the work of the Lord,

00:03:55.518 --> 00:03:58.922 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
knowing that your labor
is not in vain in connection with the Lord”

00:03:58.922 --> 00:04:03.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—plenty of work “in the work of the Lord.”

00:04:03.826 --> 00:04:05.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then when we’re doing the work

00:04:05.828 --> 00:04:08.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(and this is crucial),
as we engage in it

00:04:08.765 --> 00:04:12.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—whether it’s the preaching work
or other work assignments,

00:04:12.068 --> 00:04:15.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
if you’re in a Bethel assignment
or a construction assignment—

00:04:15.838 --> 00:04:17.941 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there’s a proper spirit.

00:04:17.941 --> 00:04:21.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And find here Romans chapter 12.

00:04:21.277 --> 00:04:24.180 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And this we see in God’s people,

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:27.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but we want to individually apply the counsel

00:04:27.917 --> 00:04:30.186 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and make sure we keep this spirit

00:04:30.186 --> 00:04:34.524 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or talk to God about it
if it’s lacking at the moment.

00:04:34.524 --> 00:04:36.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Romans chapter 12

00:04:36.926 --> 00:04:40.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and here’s what Christians are all about

00:04:40.630 --> 00:04:43.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when it comes to working for Jehovah,

00:04:43.032 --> 00:04:48.037 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
verse 11:
“Be industrious, not lazy.”

00:04:48.037 --> 00:04:52.375 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
See, Jehovah does not approve of being lazy.

00:04:53.943 --> 00:04:56.212 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Be aglow with the spirit.”

00:04:56.212 --> 00:04:57.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So you’re just absorbed with it.

00:04:57.880 --> 00:05:00.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s this zeal
—just alive with it—

00:05:00.483 --> 00:05:04.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as we slave for Jehovah.

00:05:04.087 --> 00:05:06.255 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So he appreciates

00:05:06.255 --> 00:05:10.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
an industrious, hardworking spirit,

00:05:10.460 --> 00:05:13.496 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that’s what he wants from his people.

00:05:13.496 --> 00:05:16.766 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, with all of the announcements

00:05:16.766 --> 00:05:19.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the videos
with construction going on,

00:05:19.068 --> 00:05:21.304 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I just thought I’d share this with you.

00:05:21.304 --> 00:05:24.874 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s a very special item of mine,

00:05:24.874 --> 00:05:29.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and it came up recently.

00:05:29.012 --> 00:05:31.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can see here the best you can.

00:05:31.314 --> 00:05:33.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The camera can pick it up,

00:05:33.316 --> 00:05:36.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and up here it says “Building Permit.”

00:05:36.786 --> 00:05:39.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And it’s a special memory for me, personally,

00:05:39.856 --> 00:05:42.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because as we had in some of the videos

00:05:42.525 --> 00:05:45.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when we were involved with the construction

00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:50.233 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or before construction started
with the Warwick project,

00:05:50.233 --> 00:05:54.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’d be at Tuxedo,
and a lot of work was going on

00:05:54.771 --> 00:05:58.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—preparatory—
looking for that day

00:05:58.207 --> 00:06:00.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when they could get started.

00:06:00.510 --> 00:06:03.679 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So the Governing Body
would do their best to get up

00:06:03.679 --> 00:06:08.084 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and be encouraging
(always wearing the high-vis outfits)

00:06:08.084 --> 00:06:10.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then give a spiritual talk.

00:06:10.887 --> 00:06:14.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I think it’s the only time
I’ve given a talk in high vis.

00:06:16.926 --> 00:06:19.462 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So this particular day was special

00:06:19.462 --> 00:06:22.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because things
were moving along with the community.

00:06:22.732 --> 00:06:27.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They liked us,
but I noticed Zeny (in the one video),

00:06:27.136 --> 00:06:29.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he mentioned “shovel to the ground,”

00:06:29.172 --> 00:06:30.173 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that’s OK.

00:06:30.173 --> 00:06:31.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re different.

00:06:31.174 --> 00:06:34.377 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m calling it “shovel in the ground.”

00:06:34.377 --> 00:06:37.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zeny is not from America,

00:06:37.280 --> 00:06:41.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so it means the same thing, Zeny,

00:06:41.117 --> 00:06:43.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so forgive me.

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:46.422 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I appreciate all your hard work.

00:06:46.422 --> 00:06:50.159 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But any who
have been involved with construction

00:06:50.159 --> 00:06:54.831 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(and you have a lot of folks I know here
from the former Regional Building Committee

00:06:54.831 --> 00:06:57.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—all the hardworking construction),

00:06:57.834 --> 00:07:02.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it’s always been special
to work on these spiritual projects.

00:07:02.238 --> 00:07:06.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, this particular day,
there were a lot of things going on.

00:07:06.242 --> 00:07:09.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I’m up there; it’s July 26,

00:07:09.645 --> 00:07:13.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that date is up here in the corner.

00:07:13.082 --> 00:07:15.218 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s a Friday,

00:07:15.218 --> 00:07:19.522 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and it’s the year 2013 (quite a while ago).

00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:24.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I have a talk to give to them
at 1:30 p.m. after visiting some.

00:07:25.461 --> 00:07:27.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Two hours before

00:07:29.132 --> 00:07:31.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(so it must have been around 11:30),

00:07:31.334 --> 00:07:34.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they got the building permit.

00:07:34.170 --> 00:07:37.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So the Construction Project Committee

00:07:37.974 --> 00:07:41.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(and how much we love 
those men and their wives)—

00:07:41.477 --> 00:07:43.846 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They’re there, and they said,

00:07:43.846 --> 00:07:46.482 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Well, would you mind
making this announcement?”

00:07:46.482 --> 00:07:49.051 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I thought:
‘Boy, that timing worked out good.

00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:52.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘That’s quite an honor,
the construction, you know,

00:07:52.788 --> 00:07:55.791 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and “the shovel-in-the-ground” announcement.’

00:07:55.791 --> 00:07:58.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I gave them a little spiritual side.

00:07:58.961 --> 00:08:03.366 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You know, a little glory is all right
for a human sometimes, you know.

00:08:05.601 --> 00:08:07.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So it was very exciting.

00:08:07.970 --> 00:08:10.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the memory is clear
to those who were there.

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:14.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because of the operation of holy spirit

00:08:14.243 --> 00:08:18.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the brothers
being “aglow with the spirit,” industrious,

00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:21.317 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when they made the announcement,

00:08:21.317 --> 00:08:24.053 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m telling you (those who were there),

00:08:24.053 --> 00:08:28.191 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there was joy
—the thunderous applause.

00:08:28.191 --> 00:08:30.293 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It wasn’t anything to do with me.

00:08:30.293 --> 00:08:32.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was that they got
“the shovel in the ground.”

00:08:32.828 --> 00:08:34.997 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the excitement!

00:08:34.997 --> 00:08:38.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I was able to easily walk out of there,
and they were all busy

00:08:38.868 --> 00:08:43.873 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—thrilled
over the “shovel-in-the-ground” approval.

00:08:43.873 --> 00:08:48.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, the day is coming, God willing,

00:08:48.244 --> 00:08:52.949 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the Ramapo project
to have the “shovel in the ground.”

00:08:52.949 --> 00:08:55.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You heard when they hope that happens.

00:08:55.451 --> 00:08:59.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it’s that beautiful spirit
that glorifies Jehovah

00:08:59.822 --> 00:09:01.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when they work so hard.

00:09:01.857 --> 00:09:04.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And so we have to keep that spirit.

00:09:04.694 --> 00:09:07.063 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And some could say

00:09:07.063 --> 00:09:09.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(well, it happens on occasion,

00:09:09.098 --> 00:09:13.803 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not with a lot
of God’s spiritually-minded folks):

00:09:13.803 --> 00:09:15.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Do you believe the end is coming?

00:09:15.972 --> 00:09:18.241 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“So, what are you doing all this for?

00:09:18.241 --> 00:09:21.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“If the end is really close,

00:09:21.244 --> 00:09:23.346 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what are you doing?”

00:09:23.346 --> 00:09:25.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the end is going to come

00:09:25.615 --> 00:09:28.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when Jehovah is satisfied
with the preaching work.

00:09:28.117 --> 00:09:32.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But there is also a reminder here
in Revelation chapter 7;

00:09:32.421 --> 00:09:36.158 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is always something you can forget.

00:09:36.158 --> 00:09:38.794 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I noticed Brother Butler

00:09:38.794 --> 00:09:41.597 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
touched on it in his opening prayer

00:09:41.597 --> 00:09:44.600 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(which, of course, we don’t record

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:47.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the prayers for the presentation in January),

00:09:47.136 --> 00:09:50.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but Bob touched on it.

00:09:50.273 --> 00:09:53.743 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jehovah gives us
enough to keep us focused on:

00:09:53.743 --> 00:09:56.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘You just stay busy and do my will.’

00:09:56.379 --> 00:09:59.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, this is quite fascinating

00:09:59.548 --> 00:10:02.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at chapter 7 verses 1-3:

00:10:04.487 --> 00:10:08.824 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“After this I saw four angels standing
on the four corners of the earth,

00:10:08.824 --> 00:10:10.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“holding tight the four winds of the earth,

00:10:10.826 --> 00:10:13.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so that no wind could blow on the earth

00:10:13.362 --> 00:10:16.666 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“or on the sea or on any tree.

00:10:16.666 --> 00:10:19.502 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And I saw another angel
ascending from the sunrise,

00:10:19.502 --> 00:10:21.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“having a seal of the living God;

00:10:21.804 --> 00:10:25.274 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and he called
with a loud voice to the four angels

00:10:25.274 --> 00:10:28.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to whom it was granted
to harm the earth and the sea,

00:10:28.511 --> 00:10:30.513 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“saying: [and it’s loud]

00:10:30.513 --> 00:10:34.650 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Do not harm the earth
or the sea or the trees,

00:10:34.650 --> 00:10:38.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘until after we have sealed

00:10:38.087 --> 00:10:41.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
